@Chris Purolover I see you're one of the number of those self-righteous self-appointed preachers with the scientific literacy of a 5 year old. Don't worry, your kind is all too common. You are obviously completely ignorant of every study made and book written on human sexuality in the XX century, which sadly I can't sum up here in words you would understand. Biology, ethology and zoology other areas you clearly know nothing about (though that doesn't hinder you from spewing apodictic claims related to them). In that regard, I would like to point out that there are dozens of species in the animal kingdom that practice oral sex. If you think it's not natural, take it up with the sheep, fruit bats, bears and pretty much all apes which are doing it as we speak, to list but a few. As for the biological and evolutionary purpose of oral sex, have you read anything about it before dictating that is doesn't have any? It isn't an a priori truth, you know. By the way, I'd like you to tell me what the biological purpose of abstinence is, since you're seemingly all about teleology. 

